DJMOUNT AND JDISK.DEVICE

	DJMount and JDisk.device allow the Amiga to access Amiga partitions
	on PC hard drives.  See the PC-side ADISK section to learn how to
	create Amiga partitions on PC hard drives.

	JDisk.device is a device driver which accepts trackdisk-style
	requests and passes them to the PC for processing.  You do not
	need to make any MountList entries for DJMounted drives.

	DJMount locates all Amiga partitions on PC drives and mounts
	them for use as Amiga volumes.  These Amiga volumes appear to
	the system like any other Amiga disk device, except the Amiga
	cannot autoboot from them.  The first volume will appear as
	JDisk.device unit 0, AmigaDOS volume JH0:.  The second will
	be unit 1, volume JH1:, etc.

	DJMount can be run only from the CLI or Shell, and is typically
	used in a Startup-Sequence or User-Startup file.  The Bridgeboard
	must have already been started by BindDrivers.


	COMMAND LINE

		DJMount FFS/S,DELAY/N/K

	The FFS switch forces DJMount to mount all the partitions with
	the Fast File System.  If FFS is omitted, the original file
	system will be used.  FFS will result in much better performance,
	but a lesser likelihood that a corrupted volume can be restored.

	The DELAY n value specifies how many seconds DJMount will
	wait for the PC to start up.  The default is 60 seconds.


	USING DJMOUNTED VOLUMES

	The first time you DJMount a PC hard drive partition, you will
	likely receive one or more "Not a DOS disk" requesters because
	the volume has not been AmigaDOS formatted yet.  Cancel the
	requesters.  Format each new JHx: partition, using the FFS
	option of Format if you used the FFS option on DJMount.  After
	formatting, you can use the new volumes like any other Amiga
	hard drive.  Note that you must run DJMount each time you boot
	your Amiga, since DJMount drives are not automounting or
	autobooting.  The easiest way is to place a DJMount command
	in your Startup-Sequence or User-Startup file after BindDrivers
	is run.


	THINGS YOU SHOULD NOT DO

	DON'T reboot the PC side while the Amiga is accessing a DJMounted
	volume.  You may cause the Amiga to hang, or corrupt data on the
	DJMounted volume.  It is safest to close all your Amiga
	applications and then reboot both the Amiga and PC.


	STATUS MESSAGES

DJMount: waiting n seconds for the PC to initialize - CTRL-C to abort...

	The PC side is not ready yet.  DJMount is waiting for it to
	become ready.  Should you wish to abort DJMount, press CTRL-C.

DJMount: user aborted.

	You pressed CTRL-C before the PC became ready.

DJMount: mounted n partition(s).

	DJMount has successfully mounted n partitions.
	
DJMount: timed out waiting for JanusHandler.

	DJMount waited for the full DELAY period, but the PC never became
	ready.  Lengthen the DELAY period and/or check your hardware
	and software installation.

DJMount: no Amiga partitions found.

	DJMount was unable to locate any Amiga partitions on PC hard
	drives.  Run ADISK on the PC side to turn NON-DOS partitions
	into Amiga partitions.

DJMount: devices already mounted.

	You have already successfully run DJMount.  Running it again has
	no effect.


	ERROR MESSAGES

DJMount: too many arguments
DJMount: illegal command line option.

	Something on the command line was wrong.

DJMount: DELAY value must be between 1 and 120 seconds.

	The DELAY value you specified was out of range.

DJMount: partition n must be at least 3 cylinders.

	One of the Amiga partitions is too small, and cannot be used
	by DJMount.  Run ADISK on the PC side to delete or enlarge
