LPT1

	LPT1 is used to connect the Bridgeboard's printer port emulation
	hardware to the Amiga's parallel port.  If you attempt to print
	to the Bridgeboard's LPT1: without running LPT1 first, you will
	receive device timeout errors (as if the printer was offline).

	There are no parameters for LPT1.

	LPT1 needs exclusive access to the parallel port hardware.
	If some other application is using the parallel port (either
	directly or via printer.device), that application must be closed.

	The LPT1 emulation hardware and software is intended for use with
	a printer.  Other devices (protection keys, music cards, EPROM
	programmers, etc.) which require full control of all lines of
	the parallel port will not work.  If you need access to these
	devices, you will have to purchase a parallel port card for the
	PC side and configure it as LPT2.

	The LPT1 emulation software talks directly to the Amiga's parallel
	port hardware.  Programs such as CMD (which redirects output from
	the printer.device to a file) will not work.

	Since LPT1 does not use printer.device, the printer.device escape
	sequences will not be translated through your Amiga printer driver.
	You must configure PC-side applications so that they operate your
	particular model of printer correctly.
	
