FLIPPER

	Flipper controls the floppy drive sharing hardware found
	on the A2386SX Bridgeboard.  An internal Amiga floppy drive
	can be used by both the Bridgeboard and the Amiga.

	The following must be set up before Flipper can be used:

	1) Physical cabling (whether the Amiga's DF0: or DF1: drive
	   is being shared), which includes one jumper on the A2386SX.

	2) Settings in PCPrefs, which must match the cabling and jumper
	   setting mentioned in 1).

	COMMAND LINE

		FLIPPER AUTO/S,AMIGA/S,PC/S,QUIT/S,WINDOW=/K

	TOOLTYPES

		MODE=AUTO|PC|AMIGA|QUIT
		WINDOW=xxx,yyy

	MODES

		AUTO	Flipper will attempt to read disks as AmigaDOS
			disks when they are inserted.  If it succeeds, the
			drive will be assigned to the Amiga.  Otherwise, it
			will be assigned to the	PC.

		PC	Flipper assigns the drive to the PC.  The Amiga
			can no longer see any disks in the drive.

		AMIGA	Flipper assigns the drive to the Amiga.  However,
			if the PC attempts to access the drive, it will
			succeed, but may have trouble reading and writing
			to disks.  Avoid accessing the shared drive from
			the PC side while in AMIGA mode.

		QUIT	Tells the Flipper window (if open) to close.

		The WINDOW value (xxx,yyy) specifies the location of the
		Flipper window on the Workbench screen.  The default
		location is in the upper right of the Workbench screen.
		The Flipper window will only open if MODE=AUTO.


	THE FLIPPER WINDOW

		The Flipper window will appear only if Flipper is started
		in AUTO mode.  The window contains AUTO, MAN (manual),
		Amiga drive, and PC drive gadgets.

		If the AUTO gadget is highlighted, Flipper is in AUTO mode.
		The Amiga drive and PC drive gadgets are ghosted.  Flipper
		highlights the Amiga drive or PC drive gadget depending on
		the type of disk inserted in the drive.

		If the MAN gadget is highlighted, Flipper is in MANUAL mode.
		Click on the Amiga drive or PC drive gadget to assign the
		disk drive to the Amiga or PC side.

		To change Flipper's mode, click on the MANUAL or AMIGA
		gadgets.

		When you close the Flipper window, the Flipper hardware
		stays in the state in effect at the time of closing.


	CAUTIONS

		Flipper should be placed in MANUAL PC or MANUAL AMIGA mode
		if you are using utilities which read or write foreign disk
		formats (such as CrossDOS, DOS2DOS, and some hard disk
		backup programs) to avoid confusing Flipper and the utility.

		You should also put Flipper in a MANUAL mode when
		formatting blank disks or attempting to use diskette
		repair utilities.


	STARTING FLIPPER AT BOOT TIME

		The Flipper hardware starts up in MANUAL AMIGA mode.  To
		change it to MANUAL PC or AUTO modes, you must do one of
		the following:

		1) Place a line such as the following in your
		   Startup-Sequence or User-Startup file:

			run >nil: sys:pc/flipper auto

		2) Drag a copy of the Flipper icon into the WBStartup
		   drawer (Kickstart/Workbench 2.0 only).  Select the
		   new icon, and choose Information from the Workbench
		   menu.  Set the MODE and WINDOW parameters as you'd
		   like.


	ERROR MESSAGES

	Flipper: not running, not possible to quit.

		You used the QUIT option, but Flipper was not running at
